Description:
Luxurious Northern Riverside Penthouse with two car parks
“EXPRESSIONS OF INTEREST CLOSING SATURDAY 9th FEBRUARY 2019 at 3pm”
Presiding grandly over the most magical views of the Yarra River and the CBD, this exclusive, 2 bedroom apartment is the quintessentially sophisticated inner-city lifestyle pad. Imagine a lifestyle in which you wander towards Crown Entertainment Complex for some of the city’s finest bars and dining or where you can wander in the other direction along absolute riverfront trails and parklands for a sense of tranquillity that is almost surreal for this location.
Spectacular in every regard, with a captivating angular design, this fifth floor / top floor home is architecturally brilliant and combines a breath-taking north-facing perspective with an unparalleled lifestyle experience. Fully utilising its top-floor position in this boutique, low rise block, the home evokes the feel of a penthouse and offers residents access to an impressive suite of lifestyle amenities that includes a swimming pool, gymnasium and sauna.
The home presents a particularly spacious open-plan living area equipped with granite benchtops that include a mobile island bench, as well as a Miele cooktop, an integrated refrigerator and integrated dishwasher. Savvy investors with appreciate the generous lounge / dining, two stunning balconies and well-separated bedrooms – one with ensuite - ensuring a breadth of market appeal.
Discerning down-sizers and ‘lock and leavers’ will not only relish proximity to Docklands, Southbank and the CBD, but also premium security, video entry and the luxury of two side by side parking spaces which are conveniently on the same level as the home.
Additional features includes two designer bathrooms, robes in each bedroom, central heating and cooling and a storage cage as well as access to the fitness facilities at rekdek gym.
What a unique lifestyle offering right on the fringe of Melbourne’s thriving heart!
Insights: 507/94 River Esplanade, Docklands VIC 3008 was last sold in 2002 and 275 other 2 bedroom unit in Docklands have recently been sold.

Description:
Brand new condition, Never occupied-Unrivalled Living Reveals Uninterrupted Bay and Harbour Views
Move straight in and be the fortunate first to live in this stunning 1 bedroom sky home showcasing some of Melbourne's most exhilarating, energising views. Sensationally set on the 29th floor of the award-winning, tightly held Quays complex, the uninterrupted panorama overlooks Victoria Harbour, hugging the Port Phillip Bay coastline for miles and miles of blue-water and golden-sand views.
A formal entrance hall takes you directly into a spacious open-plan living and dining area, complemented by a sleek, stone-topped kitchen fitted with high-quality Miele appliances and an integrated Fisher and Paykel fridge and dishwasher. Floor-to-ceiling glass opens up to a full-width balcony, an idyllic spot to relax, unwind and indulge with a dramatic backdrop taking in the Melbourne Star and the Bolte and West Gate Bridges. A generously sized bedroom comes complete with mirrored built-in robes, serviced by a super-stylish bathroom showcasing vibrant mosaic wall tiles.
The perfect choice for CBD professionals, market entrants and switched-on investors, the Quays building has walked away with 11 architectural, design and property awards. This is where exceptional design and effortless living intersect! Walk to the CBD, hop on a free city circle tram, or travel further afield to the MCG, Richmond, Hawthorn and all the way to Box Hill by tram. You're also moments away from Harbour Town Shopping Centre, Docklands Stadium and Costco.
Take full advantage of secure parking, concealed laundry, split-system heating and cooling, video intercom entry and this city's most impressive lifestyle facilities including a swimming pool, spa, sauna, gym and a yoga studio. Residents also enjoy exclusive access to a library, reading room, business centre, boardroom, private dining room, cinema lounge and a rooftop garden with tennis court, BBQ and dining facilities.

Description:
You won’t find better value
888 Collins Street is situated in the heart of Docklands Waterfront precinct. Designed by acclaimed architects Woods Bagot, this apartment is sure to impress the most discerning buyer.
Comprising; One bedroom, large study or 2nd bedroom option, private balcony, gourmet kitchen, sparkling bathroom, laundry complete with high quality fixtures, fittings and finishes including timber floors and Miele appliances.
Enjoy exclusive access to resident-only facilities include a swimming pool, gym, spa, library, business lounge and podium-level garden retreat.
Located on the doorstop of the central business district (CBD), the precinct enjoys all the opportunities and benefits of the world’s most liveable city.
Docklands is fast becoming the go to place for Owner Occupiers with in excess of 80% new purchasers looking to reside in the precinct.
Value for money doesn’t get any better and the time to act is now before prices start to rebound.

Description:
Your Investment Quest Stops Here!
Positioned in the fantastic Quest Docklands Serviced Apartments and offering a hassle free investment opportunity for anyone wanting a piece of the Docklands pie, this fully-furnished one bedroom apartment is one to seriously consider opposite Etihad Stadium.
Quest Docklands is an outstanding complex with some of the best management in the area. The building enjoys an incredibly high occupancy rate, while investors will love the $2200 per month (approx.) rental returns that this apartment brings in. The outgoings for this building are also very low.
The apartment itself is modern and relaxed, and offers comfortable living and meals with great light, stylish tiled kitchen with stainless steel appliances, bedroom with built-in robe and reverse cycle cooling, sleek bathroom with a European laundry, balcony with views out to Bourke Street, and ducted heating and cooling. Residents will also have access to the neighbouring gym in Victoria Point.
Enjoy all the best that the Stadium, Batman’s Hill and Victoria Harbour precincts have to offer, where you’re moments to relaxed local cafes and eateries, Docklands Park, The Hub Docklands, Victoria Harbour Promenade, trams, and Southern Cross Station.
Please contact Glenn Donnelly on 0419 998 235 to arrange an exclusive viewing.

Description:
The Entertainer
Situated in the eye catching angled Watergate residential complex is this fantastic apartment taking advantage of the corner position of the North Tower.
This 2 bedroom abode, with an expansive balcony, features an open plan dining area adjoining a galley kitchen with white colour themed cabinetry, stone benchtop, integrated stainless steel appliances including Gas stove top, electric oven and dishwashing machine.
Two spacious bedrooms, main with study alcove, have mirrored built in robes and share the stylish central bathroom incorporating laundry space. Floor to ceiling double glazed windows enable plenty of natural light.
Other features of the apartment include: ducted reverse cycle heating and cooling, security entrance and intercom entry, car park on title, cross ventilation, re-carpeted and newly painted.
The complex amenities include a 3 lane heated lap pool with spa, gymnasium and sauna, function room, and onsite manager.
Location wise, you could not be better situated. With a variety of cafes and eateries close by, you'll be spoilt for choice, while a short walk down Bourke Street also leads to Woolworths, the Post Office, and Library at the Dock. Heading in the opposite direction provides ample shopping choices with Spencer Street Outlets, or even a fun day out in the CBD.
Walking distance to Southern Cross Station, with the free tram zone basically at your doorstep, and easy access to the freeway system, what more could you ask for?

Description:
Embraced by Water, with Views to Behold!
Renowned architect John Wardle designed a residential complex which has definitely captured the hearts of its residents. This clearly shines through when you meet the occupiers that call Dock 5 home. Life is about good balance. The cantilever design and usage of many elements within Dock 5 provides a nice subtle reminder.
This large two north facing apartment, showcases the vast waters of the marina, the northern district of the city skyline, the ranges and the tequila sunsets behind the Bolte Bridge.
Spacious kitchen with stone benchtops includes peninsula bench. A perfect place to prepare home cooked meals. Integrated stainless steel appliances, incorporating gas stove top, oven, convection microwave and Asko dishwashing machine.
Superb open plan living with a separate dining area to the right for memorable dinners. Drawing your attention is the balcony with a sublime backdrop. Perfect for entertaining and relaxing. Gas plumbed for those flavoursome BBQ’s and water outlet to look after your private apartment herbs and garden.
Impressive large main bedroom with full length custom fitted robes and stylish full ensuite. 2nd bedroom shares the central bathroom with laundry facilities.
All rooms have double glazed floor to ceiling windows taking in the sights of the day and night.
Features of the apartment include
• New carpets
• Led lighting. Sensor lights in wardrobes.
• Bose Audio system
• Easy touch light switches
• Ducted heating and cooling throughout with added ceiling fans in bedrooms.
• Motorised blinds in all rooms and curtains in bedrooms
• 4 doz locker in temperature controlled room
• Secure undercover side by side car parks and large storage cage
Complex facilities include
• Communal BBQ and garden area
• Indoor heated swimming pool
• Well equipped gymnasium
• Onsite manager
• Security entrance
Free tram zoned, easy in easy out. Close to Southern cross station and the freeway network.
Post office, Library at the Dock and Woolworths a short convenient stroll away
Enjoy the many cafes and eateries in the central part of Docklands. Busy during the week quiet on the weekends.

Description:
Simply sensational resort style living!

Defined by sleek design, low-rise luxury and sweeping parkland views, this super-stylish 2 bedroom, 2 bathroom apartment in the celebrated Mosaic complex presents a rare opportunity to escape the city in peace and privacy. Description:
Rare and exclusive town living in the Yarra’s Edge precinct
Expressions Of Interest
With an abundance of truly memorable highlights from the inspired location right next to Point Park and the serene Yarra River, all the way to the stunning luxury and space you’ll find over two levels, this wonderful 3 bedroom + study, 2 bathroom townhouse is an irresistible Docklands offering.
This seldom offered modern oasis has all buyers in mind, from young professionals who want a base not far from work in the CBD or Southbank, to retirees on the hunt for a gorgeous downsizer. A ground level dazzles with a generous north-facing courtyard at the front of the property, which promises a tranquil space to enjoy the park views over dinners and weekend cocktails.
Inside, the spacious living and dining zone is adjoined by the immaculate stone kitchen which offers an island bench, great storage, and stainless steel appliances. Downstairs also promises a bedroom with BIR which sits next to the stylish bathroom and European laundry. The top level has two more bedrooms with BIRs including one with access to a north balcony, quality 2nd bathroom, and a study/home office with storage which could also be a quaint 4th bedroom.
Other features include ducted heating and cooling, secure intercom, two secure car spaces, and access to Yarra Point facilities including a 300 sqm rooftop herb garden complete with BBQ facilities, plus a residents’ lounge, gym, and business centre. In addition to free access to RekDek facilities, include a gymnasium, 25m indoor heated lap pool, spa, sauna and steam room.
Nearby South Wharf restaurants will be a delight all year round, whether you’re grabbing some beers and schnitzel at Munich Brauhaus or some tasty Pad Thai at the lively Bangpop. Other nearby attractions include Crown Entertainment Complex with world class restaurants, IGA X-Press supermarket, and Southbank, South Melbourne, and Port Melbourne attractions.

Description:
Well below replacement cost
888 Collins Street is situated in the heart of Docklands Waterfront precinct. Designed by acclaimed architects Woods Bagot, this apartment is sure to impress the most discerning buyer.
Comprising; two bedrooms, private balcony, gourmet kitchen, sparkling bathroom, laundry, complete with high quality fixtures, fittings and finishes including timber floors and Miele appliances.
Enjoy exclusive access to resident-only facilities include a swimming pool, gym, spa, library, business lounge and podium-level garden retreat.
Located on the doorstop of the central business district (CBD), the precinct enjoys all the opportunities and benefits of the world’s most liveable city.
Docklands is fast becoming the go to place for Owner Occupiers with in excess of 80% new purchasers looking to reside in the precinct.
Value for money doesn’t get any better and the time to act is now before prices start to rebound.

Description:
Very Spacious With Direct Water & City Views
Perfection and opulence combine in this North facing light filled modern luxury located in the highly sought-after Yarra's Edge precinct. Superbly spacious and nestled on level 36 this luxuriously appointed Mirvac sub penthouse is approx 216sq in total with floor to ceiling windows providing spectacular uninterrupted vistas of Melbourne's City Skyline over the Yarra's Edge marina all the way to Southbank. The views are beautiful by day and dazzling by night. Step inside and you will be led past two spacious bedrooms with built in robes which are conveniently serviced by a lavish central bathroom, a huge master bedroom which includes a luxurious en-suite with bathtub and ample storage space, a designer kitchen accentuated by the large superbly spacious open plan living flowing to a casual dining area, a very large terrace handy for entertaining guests while watching the perfect sunset. Additional features include double glazed windows, three secure car spaces, large storage cage, ducted air conditioning and heating along with the use of the Rek Dek gymnasium, indoor pool, steam room, spa, and sauna.
For private inspection Call Richard 0437 250 964

Description:
Brand New and Uninterrupted Northerly Views in the Aqui Promenade
Brilliant northern views and wonderful modern charisma are the hallmarks of this sensational 2 bedroom apartment which sits on the 20th floor of the ‘Gold Tower’ building in the excellent Aqui development.
With a low-maintenance layout and ready for a variety of buyers, this utterly relaxed retreat is highlighted by a charming open living and meals zone, stone kitchen with an immaculate feel and premium Asko appliances. North-facing balcony with views of the Melbourne Star Observation Wheel and mountains in the distance. Bedrooms with BIRs, and a gorgeous bathroom with rain shower and laundry.
Other features include reverse cycle heating and cooling, secure intercom, secure car space, and access to a 25m indoor pool, spa, sauna, gym, library, private meeting rooms, and rooftop garden. Close to The District Docklands, harbourside restaurants, Ron Barassi Snr Park, Marvel Stadium, and the 30, 70, and 86 trams. An appealing Docklands opportunity that shouldn’t be missed!
To arrange an inspection, please contact Vicky Leong on 0452 486 860.

Description:
Designer Docklands Living with Inspired Views
Stunning with remarkable views of Victoria Harbour, Marvel Stadium, and the iconic CBD, this two bedroom, two bathroom Palladio apartment with a design by renowned architects Fender Katsalidis is blissful NewQuay Precinct living.
You’ll never get sick of the amazing water and CBD views which are best enjoyed from the main balcony, which is accessed via the living and meals zone and is a sensational space for weekend dinners and drinks which will become part of your weekly routine. There are also two additional balconies with views which each have excellent privacy and are located off the bedrooms.
A stone-featured kitchen is equipped with stainless steel appliances and timber cabinetry. The master bedroom has excellent built-in robe storage, a study nook, and a striking ensuite, while the 2nd bedroom also comes with a BIR. Further living highlights include an attractive bathroom, European laundry, ducted heating and cooling, secure intercom, secure car space, and access to a health club with rooftop pool, gym, and private function area.
Moments to restaurants including Oscar’s Table, Renzo’s Bar Café Italiano, and Fish Bar, IGA supermarket, The District Docklands, and the 30, 70, and 86 trams. This stylish Palladio apartment is calling your name, so don’t miss out on this terrific opportunity!
Please contact Thomas Tregonning on 0413 317 304 to arrange an exclusive viewing.
